<br>
I'd sure appreciate some info as I don't wanna start tossing Gobobner around and shooting bolts at the wrong mobs... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uthemadlimper.showPublicProfile?language=EN>The Mad Limper</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://gifs123.tripod.com/page11/monster10.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#333333>(4/13/01 8:30:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=47.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://gifs123.tripod.com/page11/monster10.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Wizards in 3rd Gate - what's the scoop?</span><hr size=1> Ahhh I figured it out, so I guess I'll answer my own questions if anybody else is curious.  BTW, I'm a DE....and it's worth the faction hits.  I got 3 1/2 yellow bubs today in 51, compared to the 1 bub exp I got spending 9 hours in skyfire nonstop action paired with a 55 shamy.<br>
<br>
Liskvan Xlottl, lvl 40 wizard, spawns p1231 n1646 10minutes.  Melee's for 112, 1773hps unbuffed.  <br>
<br>
Evin Xlottl, lvl 40 wizard, spawns p1306 n1644 10minutes.  Melees for 112, 1773hps unbuffed.  <br>
<br>
Krizin J'Narus, lvl 40 Necro, spawns p734 n1727, 10 minutes.  Melees for 112, 1773hps unbuffed, never summons a pet.<br>
<br>
Faction hits are: TheDead, QueenofAtheroxex(spel)<br>
<br>
These faction hits put you KOS with:<br>
<br>
3rd Gate:  <br>
<br>
(1) Kszan Punox, lvl 40 guard SK, roams between cleric guild entrance and down by the two guards at the gates near library.  Does not see invis, extremely long range aggro and HT.<br>
(2) Entire Necro guild, duh.  I did not check out the npc in the library which summons a necro pet, as I think I remember him being a quest NPC i.e. damn near unkillable.<br>
<br>
Commons:<br>
(1) Olavn N'Mar - lvl 40'ish wizard, guarding the entrance to the Guild Hall.  Fairly wide aggro range, DOES see through invis.  I did not venture into the guild past this npc to see if others are KOS.  If you can kill these mugs, you had better have already bought all the spells you need if you are a DE.<br>
<br>
Foreign Quarter:<br>
(1) Two wizard guards, lvl 40'ish, they are on the roof of the main entry area with the first lift gate.  They do NOT see invis.<br>
<br>
All &quot;guards&quot; i.e. named Guard Tolus, etc, have no faction relation.  No merchants have any faction relation, except possibly those in the guilds.  As a DE now KOS to them, it's still very possible to call Neriak my home, the only place of interest is the bank, gem vendor and a merchant or two...all of which are still &quot;warmly&quot;.<br>
<br>
I have absolutely no idea yet if faction is shared amongst all necro guilds, but will find out the hard way I presume.<br>
<br>
Magic resistances:  I never had a lava bolt resisted, though I quit using it in favor of 44shock after about an hour.  The shock was outright resisted one time, and partially resisted perhaps 3 times out of 6 hours nonstop action.  It's important to attack them the instant they pop or they will all buff themselves making it that much harder to KS your pet.  I prefered earth for the root, tried air but it sucks going invis i.e. the mob doesn't hit it when it spawns on top of it, did not try water or fire as I enjoyed staying out of melee range via root.<br>
<br>
My MR is 81 with shielding up, and it made a huge difference.  I outright resisted at least 50% of everything tossed at me, while never seeming to take full damage when I got hit.  The Necro Krizin managed to land Fear on me 3 times, which sucks because by the time it wears off, your pet has killed it and sucked your exp. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uzaknafinis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zaknafinis</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 144<br> <font color=#333333>(4/13/01 11:56:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=47.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Wizards in 3rd Gate - what's the scoop?</span><hr size=1> I recommend having your new Summon Companion spell memmed.  Your pet will get feared at times and pathing will take him straight to the SK that wanders near the gates and the clerics guild.  Nuke Hard to kill the Necro and then start summoning like mad because that SK is hell on wheels.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><a href=mailto:Zaknafinis@Hotmail.com>Zaknafinis Convoquer (55th level Conjurer)</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uallisster.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Allisster</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#333333>(4/16/01 5:10:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=47.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=