<br>
As for your home town faction, screw it <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .  How much time do you actually spend there?  Ya only really need to go back to get your spells and train.  at 50+ spells arent even found there anymore, and im preaty sure there is another place besides neriak a DE mage can train (im thinking the outpost).  Anyway, doing this wont even get you kos with the magician guild, or almost any part other part of neriak besides the stuff your killing (unless ya do the guard, which ya dont need to if your not KoS).  If ya do both wizzies and the necro, ya should only be kos to the wizzies, the necro, and parts of the necro guild.  Maybe a few other things.  Ya will be fine in the rest of your town.  Even if ya do kos to guards, ya can just invis to your guild then drop it to train (no guards in mage guild i dont think).  Ive been kos in WFP (where my guild is) and EFP since I was 34 (Freeport is my home town).  To train i just invis to guild then drop it.  If i need to buy stuff, i just invis to the vendors house, then drop it.  A few vendors by the guards, but they dont sell anything ya cant find somewhere else in the zone.  And if its just one guard or two guards, I kill them then do my trading.<br>
<br>
BTW: my new strat on wizzies is:  Kill fisrt wizzy.  Wait 3-5minutes, kill next one.  Then kill the guard.  Then wait for next wizzie (usually preaty soon after guard is gone).  Kill both wizzies.  Then since guard is still dead I go kill the necro quickly, then go back to wizzies.  So i do 2 wizzies, then rotate the necro and guard.  If ya not kos to guard, just do necro everytime.  At 53 i used 2 chars to outdamage.  54 i use 1 char 1 scars. <p><table border="0" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="1">
